* Foundations Modules: <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/curricula/foundation-modules/what-is-web-accessibility/" rel="external">Module 1: What is Web Accessibility</a>; <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/curricula/foundation-modules/people-and-digital-technology/" rel="external">Module 2: People and Digital Technology</a>; <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/curricula/foundation-modules/business-case-and-benefits/" rel="external">Module 3: Business Case and Benefits</a>; <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/curricula/foundation-modules/principles-standards-and-checks/" rel="external">Module 4: Principles, Standards, and Checks</a>; <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/curricula/foundation-modules/getting-started-with-accessibility/" rel="external">Module 5: Getting Started with Accessibility</a>
* Developer Modules: 
* Designer Modules: 





Language
: 
English (English)




Format

: Face-to-face - all teaching sessions are provided on-site
